import{_ as t,c as o,o as a,a5 as n}from"./chunks/framework.g0c4JhLR.js";const p=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"data/news/26/01/28/gov-vs-citizens/input/cbc.ca.md","filePath":"data/news/26/01/28/gov-vs-citizens/input/cbc.ca.md"}'),i={name:"data/news/26/01/28/gov-vs-citizens/input/cbc.ca.md"};function s(r,e,d,l,c,h){return a(),o("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[n("<p>2 federal agents fired shots when Alex Pretti was killed in Minneapolis: U.S. official Trump staffer walks back statement calling Pretti &#39;an assassin&#39;</p><p>The Associated Press · Posted: Jan 27, 2026 8:32 PM EST | Last Updated: 7 hours ago A photo of a bearded man sits among candles and flowers A photo of Alex Pretti, who was fatally shot in Minneapolis over the weekend, is displayed at the shooting scene Monday. A Border patrol official says two federal agents fired shots during the encounter. (Adam Gray/The Associated Press) Two federal officers fired shots during the encounter that killed ICU nurse Alex Pretti in Minneapolis, a U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) official told Congress in a notice sent Tuesday.</p><p>Officers tried to take Pretti into custody and he resisted, leading to a struggle, according to a notification to Congress obtained by The Associated Press. During the struggle, a Border Patrol agent yelled, &quot;He&#39;s got a gun!&quot; multiple times, the official said.</p><p>A Border Patrol agent and a CBP officer each fired Glock pistols, the notice said. (The U.S. Border Patrol is a federal agency under CBP.)</p><p>Investigators from CBP&#39;s Office of Professional Responsibility conducted the analysis based on a review of body-worn camera footage and agency documentation, the notice said. The law requires the agency to inform relevant congressional committees about deaths in CBP custody within 72 hours.</p><p>The notification came a day after U.S. President Donald Trump ordered border czar Tom Homan to take over his administration&#39;s immigration crackdown in Minnesota following Pretti&#39;s death, which was the second fatal shooting in Minneapolis this month of a person at the hands of federal law enforcement.</p><p>WATCH | Why Bovino was moved out of Minnesota:</p><p>Why is Border Patrol commander Greg Bovino being removed from Minnesota?</p><p>Andrew Chang explains why U.S. Border Patrol commander Greg Bovino is leaving Minnesota as President Donald Trump shakes up his immigration crackdown leadership — following ICE agents&#39; involvement in a second fatal shooting in Minneapolis. Images provided by The Canadian Press, Reuters and Getty Images By sending Homan to Minnesota, &quot;we&#39;re going to de-escalate a little bit,&quot; Trump said during an interview on Fox News. The president added of Homan, &quot;Tom, as tough as he is, gets along&quot; with governors and mayors, even in Democratic areas.</p><p>As he left the White House on Tuesday, Trump was asked whether Pretti&#39;s killing was justified. He responded by saying that a &quot;big investigation&quot; was underway. In the hours after Pretti&#39;s death, some administration officials sought to blame the shooting on the 37-year-old intensive care nurse.</p><p>Stephen Miller, Trump&#39;s deputy chief of staff who had initially called Pretti &quot;an assassin,&quot; issued a statement suggesting CBP officers in Minneapolis &quot;may not have been following&quot; protocol. He said the Homeland Security Department&#39;s initial statements about what transpired on Saturday was &quot;based on reports from CBP on the ground.&quot;</p><p>Agents try to enter consulate</p><p>Ecuador&#39;s minister of foreign affairs, meanwhile, filed a protest with the U.S. Embassy after ICE agents tried to enter the Ecuadorian consulate in Minneapolis without permission Tuesday.</p><p>A video of the attempt on social media shows a consulate staffer running to the door to turn the ICE agents away, telling them, &quot;This is the Ecuadorian consulate. You&#39;re not allowed to enter.&quot; One ICE officer can be heard responding by threatening to &quot;grab&quot; the staffer if he touched the agent before agreeing to leave.</p><p>WATCH | Trump signals plans to &#39;de-escalate&#39; Minnesota ICE crackdown:</p><p>Trump pledges to ease tensions in Minneapolis as crackdowns continue</p><p>U.S. President Donald Trump has promised to ease tensions in Minneapolis even as immigration crackdowns continue and he criticized one of the people shot and killed by federal agents. International law generally prohibits law enforcement authorities from entering foreign consulates or embassies without permission, though sometimes permission may be assumed granted for life-threatening emergencies, like fires.</p><p>&quot;Consulate officials immediately prevented the ICE officer from entering the consular building, thus ensuring the protection of the Ecuadorians who were present at the time and activating the emergency protocols issued by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Human Mobility,&quot; the ministry wrote on X.</p><p>A &quot;note of protest&quot; was filed with the U.S. Embassy in Ecuador so that similar attempts aren&#39;t made at other consulates, the ministry said. The State Department, Homeland Security and Immigration and Customs Enforcement did not immediately respond to the AP&#39;s requests for comment.</p>",19)])])}const f=t(i,[["render",s]]);export{p as __pageData,f as default};
